WEBVTT

1
00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:48.570
[Uncle]

2
00:00:58.440 --> 00:00:59.630
[Switching off]

3
00:01:20.710 --> 00:01:22.900
[Room 504] [Prosecutor Yoon Gyuho]
[Investigators: Choi Ara. Go Yijeong]

4
00:01:23.250 --> 00:01:24.570
Yes. come in.

5
00:01:26.270 --> 00:01:27.980
Wow. What brings you here

6
00:01:28.190 --> 00:01:29.789
so early in the morning?

7
00:01:30.190 --> 00:01:31.320
I have a favor to ask.

8
00:01:31.500 --> 00:01:32.060
To ask me?

9
00:01:32.210 --> 00:01:32.970
For who?

10
00:01:33.390 --> 00:01:34.350
You?

11
00:01:34.520 --> 00:01:36.509
There's a jerk who annoys me.

12
00:01:36.820 --> 00:01:37.710
Who?

13
00:01:42.530 --> 00:01:43.860
His name is Hong Sungho.

14
00:01:44.210 --> 00:01:46.610
He runs a laundry business.
Not a small shop

15
00:01:46.920 --> 00:01:48.320
but a commercial company

16
00:01:48.440 --> 00:01:50.440
that deals with corporate clients.

17
00:01:55.100 --> 00:01:57.229
Dig into him until you find something.

18
00:01:57.520 --> 00:02:00.680
You're the expert in
corporate and economic cases. after all.

19
00:02:00.680 --> 00:02:02.220
How has

20
00:02:02.380 --> 00:02:04.440
this person upset you?

21
00:02:05.260 --> 00:02:07.880
He messed with someone important to me.

22
00:02:08.479 --> 00:02:10.600
so I'm going to pay him back.

23
00:02:10.880 --> 00:02:12.080
That's a first.

24
00:02:12.200 --> 00:02:14.330
You have someone important to you now?

25
00:02:15.890 --> 00:02:17.310
I know. right?

26
00:02:17.550 --> 00:02:20.480
Besides. don't you hate
targeted investigations?

27
00:02:20.640 --> 00:02:23.100
There are always exceptions. aren't there?

28
00:02:24.050 --> 00:02:25.370
So you are human.

29
00:02:25.720 --> 00:02:28.090
I'll return the favor. I promise.

30
00:02:37.950 --> 00:02:38.840
OK.

31
00:02:39.730 --> 00:02:40.900
Thanks.

32
00:02:41.240 --> 00:02:42.970
So. who's this important person

33
00:02:42.970 --> 00:02:44.570
you're protecting?

34
00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:47.450
[Investigator. Lee Chaeha]

35
00:02:47.450 --> 00:02:49.400
I'll leave it to you. Yoon.

36
00:02:49.810 --> 00:02:51.180
-Bye.
-Hey. hey. hey!

37
00:02:51.420 --> 00:02:52.510
Who is it?

38
00:02:53.329 --> 00:02:54.230
Dude...

39
00:02:58.130 --> 00:02:59.180
Hello?

40
00:02:59.390 --> 00:03:00.500
Where are you?

41
00:03:01.020 --> 00:03:03.820
Do I have to report my whereabouts to you?

42
00:03:04.250 --> 00:03:05.490
I'm sorry.

43
00:03:05.660 --> 00:03:08.750
Instead of calling me.
shouldn't you be rushing to work?

44
00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:10.690
My phone was off.

45
00:03:10.800 --> 00:03:12.190
so I got up late.

46
00:03:12.360 --> 00:03:14.720
Excuses on top of neglecting your duties?

47
00:03:15.290 --> 00:03:16.500
I'm sorry.

48
00:03:16.790 --> 00:03:17.890
Don't come to work.

49
00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:19.360
No! I'll be right there...

50
00:03:19.510 --> 00:03:20.300
Ah!

51
00:03:25.630 --> 00:03:26.610
Don't come.

52
00:03:27.070 --> 00:03:28.450
Why are you doing this?

53
00:03:28.670 --> 00:03:31.120
Did I do something wrong yesterday?

54
00:03:31.730 --> 00:03:34.340
Don't come to the office.
Go straight to the scene.

55
00:03:34.340 --> 00:03:35.270
Can you do that?

56
00:03:35.520 --> 00:03:36.620
Oh...

57
00:03:37.120 --> 00:03:39.480
Yes. got it.

58
00:04:08.350 --> 00:04:10.350
Are you out of your mind. Lee Chaeha?

59
00:04:17.490 --> 00:04:19.690
Don't look at me. I don't want to see you.

60
00:04:25.690 --> 00:04:27.810
[Park Siwoo]

61
00:04:30.320 --> 00:04:32.610
[Kim Yunsik]

62
00:04:38.020 --> 00:04:39.690
[Kwak Seunghwan:
because of property division?]

63
00:04:40.340 --> 00:04:41.970
[Kim (Koryoin): drug overdose]

64
00:04:42.260 --> 00:04:43.800
[Found in a small room
on the second floor]

65
00:04:43.990 --> 00:04:46.170
[Last abandoned mine in Danhyeon
to be converted into a casino...]

66
00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:48.840
[Danhyeon Land construction led by Ohsong:
casino. hotel. theme park. resort...]

67
00:04:48.970 --> 00:04:51.170
[First female executive
in the casino industry...]

68
00:04:51.170 --> 00:04:53.370
[Promises "transparent management
and regional win-win"]

69
00:04:53.590 --> 00:04:55.240
[Danhyeon City "Casino Owner Murdered";
his driver. Lee. a suspect]

70
00:05:01.810 --> 00:05:04.100
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

71
00:05:13.020 --> 00:05:14.020
Mr. Lee!

72
00:05:14.900 --> 00:05:15.710
Mr. Song.

73
00:05:15.850 --> 00:05:17.050
when did you get here?

74
00:05:17.460 --> 00:05:18.990
I've been here all morning.

75
00:05:20.890 --> 00:05:22.060
Where's the knife?

76
00:05:24.680 --> 00:05:28.080
Then we need to find other evidence
to prove the crime.

77
00:05:28.540 --> 00:05:30.710
The culprit really thought this through.

78
00:05:30.710 --> 00:05:32.730
even trying to frame an ex-convict.

79
00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:43.990
Why do you think she killed him?

80
00:05:44.480 --> 00:05:46.670
Killing a spouse.
it's usually one of the two:

81
00:05:46.670 --> 00:05:48.270
cheating or life insurance.

82
00:05:49.370 --> 00:05:50.909
Which one is better?

83
00:05:51.720 --> 00:05:52.670
What?

84
00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:54.810
Which one I think it is?

85
00:05:55.300 --> 00:05:56.270
No.

86
00:05:57.130 --> 00:06:00.210
Which one do you think is better?

87
00:06:03.640 --> 00:06:06.150
His mom killed his dad.

88
00:06:06.340 --> 00:06:07.680
To the kid.

89
00:06:09.920 --> 00:06:12.620
which one is better?

90
00:06:16.300 --> 00:06:18.020
I prefer life insurance.

91
00:06:18.650 --> 00:06:20.850
Let's look for the insurance certificate.

92
00:06:20.850 --> 00:06:23.210
-I'll look in the yard.
-OK.

93
00:06:39.470 --> 00:06:40.409
Who is it!

94
00:06:49.659 --> 00:06:52.130
How did you get in here. kid?

95
00:06:52.250 --> 00:06:53.870
You can't just come in here.

96
00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:54.850
Why?

97
00:06:54.990 --> 00:06:56.140
This is my home.

98
00:06:56.670 --> 00:06:59.270
Uh... well...

99
00:06:59.409 --> 00:07:01.800
I came just to take this.

100
00:07:01.920 --> 00:07:03.520
Look. isn't it cool?

101
00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:05.540
Yes. it's cool.

102
00:07:05.690 --> 00:07:07.340
I'm bringing it on my trip.

103
00:07:08.250 --> 00:07:09.220
Are you going on a trip?

104
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:09.850
Yes!

105
00:07:10.050 --> 00:07:12.120
I'm taking a plane and going far away!

106
00:07:12.300 --> 00:07:13.450
Exciting. right?

107
00:07:14.820 --> 00:07:17.420
Um. can you brag to me?

108
00:07:17.800 --> 00:07:18.730
When are you leaving?

109
00:07:18.730 --> 00:07:19.860
Where are you going?

110
00:07:19.900 --> 00:07:20.930
With whom?

111
00:07:20.990 --> 00:07:22.250
With my mom...

112
00:07:22.450 --> 00:07:23.360
Ahn Jinwoo!

113
00:07:23.620 --> 00:07:24.630
Mom!

114
00:07:25.370 --> 00:07:28.300
Who said you could come here
without telling me. huh?

115
00:07:28.510 --> 00:07:31.570
I just wanted to get this.

116
00:07:32.970 --> 00:07:35.430
I was worried about you.

117
00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:38.860
Hello.

118
00:07:42.730 --> 00:07:44.580
What are you doing here?

119
00:07:45.370 --> 00:07:48.170
We're looking for more traces
left by Lee Hyunsoo.

120
00:07:49.270 --> 00:07:50.630
At my house?

121
00:07:50.909 --> 00:07:54.430
Yes.

122
00:07:55.409 --> 00:07:56.740
Are you staying nearby?

123
00:07:57.000 --> 00:07:59.460
Yes. my sister lives nearby.

124
00:08:00.400 --> 00:08:04.600
But... isn't there enough evidence
to convict Lee Hyunsoo?

125
00:08:05.080 --> 00:08:06.620
You even have his knife.

126
00:08:06.820 --> 00:08:07.730
Yes. but before

127
00:08:07.920 --> 00:08:09.150
drafting the indictment.

128
00:08:09.150 --> 00:08:11.770
we sometimes conduct
a final survey of the scene ourselves.

129
00:08:11.770 --> 00:08:13.180
Please put him in jail ASAP.

130
00:08:13.180 --> 00:08:14.660
Mr. Lee! I found...

131
00:08:20.900 --> 00:08:21.820
Hello.

132
00:08:22.350 --> 00:08:23.730
Jinwoo. let's go.

133
00:08:25.950 --> 00:08:26.910
Goodbye.

134
00:08:27.580 --> 00:08:29.600
Bye. kiddo!

135
00:08:32.270 --> 00:08:33.130
Did you find it?

136
00:08:33.220 --> 00:08:34.110
Yes.

137
00:08:35.140 --> 00:08:37.770
A life insurance
worth 150 million won (~$100k)

138
00:08:37.770 --> 00:08:40.090
[Nuri Life Insurance]
[The Insured: Ahn Dongjin]

139
00:08:38.370 --> 00:08:40.770
under the name of her husband.
Ahn Dongjin.

140
00:08:40.929 --> 00:08:41.799
Let's go too.

141
00:08:41.980 --> 00:08:42.630
OK.

142
00:08:46.540 --> 00:08:48.510
[Prosecution]

143
00:08:49.100 --> 00:08:52.470
Han Soojin saw you
resurveying the crime scene?

144
00:08:52.790 --> 00:08:53.570
Yes.

145
00:08:53.830 --> 00:08:56.160
but she didn't seem to trust us at all.

146
00:08:56.510 --> 00:08:58.710
Looks like we need to get a warrant soon.

147
00:08:59.030 --> 00:09:00.090
Where's the knife?

148
00:09:00.290 --> 00:09:01.650
We couldn't find it.

149
00:09:04.310 --> 00:09:05.700
-Mr. Song.
-Yes?

150
00:09:05.910 --> 00:09:09.040
Get the police to stake her out

151
00:09:09.170 --> 00:09:11.500
so we don't lose sight of her.

152
00:09:11.640 --> 00:09:13.410
Is that really necessary?

153
00:09:13.530 --> 00:09:15.260
The police will be annoyed too.

154
00:09:15.370 --> 00:09:16.960
That's not important.

155
00:09:17.490 --> 00:09:20.730
It's better than her escaping.

156
00:09:20.840 --> 00:09:21.810
Oh?

157
00:09:22.280 --> 00:09:25.380
Mr. Lee. I thought you were Mr. Ju!

158
00:09:25.630 --> 00:09:27.960
You two are
rubbing off on each other. huh?

159
00:09:31.180 --> 00:09:32.270
You think so?

160
00:09:32.430 --> 00:09:34.020
-Mr. Song.
-Yes?

161
00:09:34.320 --> 00:09:37.250
Please call the police
and request the stakeout now.

162
00:09:37.580 --> 00:09:39.230
Oh. yes. right away.

163
00:09:45.280 --> 00:09:48.190
I'm requesting a stakeout on Han Soojin.

164
00:09:53.610 --> 00:09:54.590
Director Tak.

165
00:09:57.100 --> 00:09:58.330
Investigator Lee Chaeha?

166
00:09:58.330 --> 00:09:59.320
Nice to meet you.

167
00:10:00.230 --> 00:10:01.400
Hello.

168
00:10:02.180 --> 00:10:04.520
This is Director Tak Sungwoong
from Criminal Division 2.

169
00:10:04.520 --> 00:10:05.550
Sit. sit.

170
00:10:06.180 --> 00:10:07.120
Here.

171
00:10:07.310 --> 00:10:08.150
Goodness.

172
00:10:11.670 --> 00:10:13.040
I heard you used to be a cop.

173
00:10:13.040 --> 00:10:14.520
Yes. that's right.

174
00:10:14.750 --> 00:10:15.480
I see.

175
00:10:15.750 --> 00:10:17.080
How are you settling in?

176
00:10:17.560 --> 00:10:19.240
It's been good.

177
00:10:19.690 --> 00:10:21.270
He's pretty picky.

178
00:10:21.440 --> 00:10:22.970
so not many people make the cut.

179
00:10:22.970 --> 00:10:24.780
You must be really good at your job.

180
00:10:24.780 --> 00:10:26.070
He is.

181
00:10:28.620 --> 00:10:30.880
Please take good care of Taeseon.

182
00:10:30.940 --> 00:10:32.410
He's like my own son.

183
00:10:33.600 --> 00:10:34.610
Alright.

184
00:10:34.950 --> 00:10:36.810
I shouldn't overstay my welcome.

185
00:10:37.560 --> 00:10:38.720
I'm off.

186
00:10:39.840 --> 00:10:41.040
Get on with your work.

187
00:10:47.940 --> 00:10:48.940
Are you OK?

188
00:10:49.130 --> 00:10:50.180
I'm so sorry!

189
00:10:51.410 --> 00:10:52.300
Oh no...

190
00:10:52.480 --> 00:10:53.640
I'm fine.

191
00:10:54.560 --> 00:10:55.750
-Mr. Song.
-Yes?

192
00:10:56.020 --> 00:10:57.590
Can you get the mop in the restroom?

193
00:10:57.590 --> 00:10:59.100
Yes. I'll get it.

194
00:11:03.530 --> 00:11:04.570
Are you soaked?

195
00:11:05.390 --> 00:11:06.470
N-No.

196
00:11:08.340 --> 00:11:10.810
Gosh. you're all wet.

197
00:11:11.870 --> 00:11:13.580
Oh. it's not that wet.

198
00:11:25.090 --> 00:11:26.900
What... What are you doing?

199
00:11:29.820 --> 00:11:31.020
What do you think?

200
00:11:31.640 --> 00:11:33.040
Taking off your clothes.

201
00:11:37.780 --> 00:11:39.480
How do you want to handle it?

202
00:11:40.930 --> 00:11:42.390
Have you thought about it?

203
00:11:44.260 --> 00:11:45.640
I'm sorry.

204
00:11:46.200 --> 00:11:48.840
I was drunk. It was a mistake.

205
00:11:50.110 --> 00:11:51.640
What are you talking about?

206
00:11:51.840 --> 00:11:53.440
I mean. Lee Gilyoung's case.

207
00:11:53.710 --> 00:11:55.970
Are you on board with the investigation?

208
00:11:56.050 --> 00:11:58.060
You didn't answer me after that day.

209
00:11:58.800 --> 00:11:59.790
Oh...

210
00:12:02.060 --> 00:12:03.210
I am on board.

211
00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:05.170
And...

212
00:12:05.880 --> 00:12:07.230
A mistake?

213
00:12:09.070 --> 00:12:11.560
So that was a mistake to you?

214
00:12:12.010 --> 00:12:13.880
How could you make such a mistake?

215
00:12:14.350 --> 00:12:15.290
Oh.

216
00:12:15.940 --> 00:12:17.340
Do you just kiss anyone

217
00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:19.770
whenever you've had a few?

218
00:12:20.090 --> 00:12:21.620
I'm not that kind of person!

219
00:12:21.760 --> 00:12:23.290
When I said it was a mistake.

220
00:12:23.370 --> 00:12:25.810
I don't mean that
it meant nothing to me...

221
00:12:25.960 --> 00:12:27.620
It wasn't a mistake on my part.

222
00:12:29.860 --> 00:12:30.810
What?

223
00:12:32.670 --> 00:12:35.250
Do I look like someone
who'd have a lapse of judgement?

224
00:12:35.250 --> 00:12:37.180
It wasn't a drunken mistake for me.

225
00:12:39.540 --> 00:12:40.730
Then...

226
00:12:42.320 --> 00:12:43.470
Sex partners.

227
00:12:49.300 --> 00:12:50.190
Right.

228
00:12:50.850 --> 00:12:52.180
I apologize if I gave you

229
00:12:52.270 --> 00:12:53.370
the wrong idea.

230
00:12:53.760 --> 00:12:54.790
But

231
00:12:55.990 --> 00:12:58.780
do you really think I'd ever fall for you?

232
00:13:00.080 --> 00:13:02.940
I'd prefer if you actually
had a lapse of judgement.

233
00:13:03.130 --> 00:13:05.160
Think whatever you want.

234
00:13:05.850 --> 00:13:07.730
But don't push it on me.

235
00:13:09.890 --> 00:13:10.960
I got the mop...

236
00:13:15.030 --> 00:13:16.430
What are you waiting for?

237
00:13:16.700 --> 00:13:18.040
Go get changed.

238
00:13:18.370 --> 00:13:20.840
I have a spare shirt in my office.

239
00:13:21.520 --> 00:13:22.470
Yes.

240
00:13:37.510 --> 00:13:40.570
We'll arrest Han Soojin
once we locate her.

241
00:13:40.800 --> 00:13:43.990
Send the request for an arrest warrant.
with the evidence.

242
00:13:43.990 --> 00:13:44.990
Also.

243
00:13:45.350 --> 00:13:47.160
check around the hardware store.

244
00:13:47.160 --> 00:13:49.930
See if there's a place
the Koryoin. Kim. could've stayed at.

245
00:13:49.930 --> 00:13:51.220
Got it.

246
00:13:52.940 --> 00:13:53.760
Right.

247
00:13:58.900 --> 00:13:59.900
And this.

248
00:14:07.900 --> 00:14:10.760
Information I collected
on Kang Woosung's murder.

249
00:14:11.370 --> 00:14:13.910
I'm eager to see
what you can do this time. too.

250
00:14:14.200 --> 00:14:15.600
Mr. Lee.

251
00:14:22.010 --> 00:14:22.900
Yes.

252
00:14:23.080 --> 00:14:26.940
this is Investigator Lee Chaeha
from Criminal Div. 1. West District.

253
00:14:28.960 --> 00:14:30.300
What about her phone?

254
00:14:31.450 --> 00:14:33.020
I see. OK.

255
00:14:33.160 --> 00:14:34.890
Let me know when you locate her.

256
00:14:44.720 --> 00:14:47.740
Her son said they were going on a trip.
somewhere far.

257
00:14:48.100 --> 00:14:49.820
Seems like she planned on going on a trip

258
00:14:49.820 --> 00:14:51.680
with the life insurance payout.

259
00:14:52.720 --> 00:14:56.010
Or maybe she's planning
to kill herself with her son.

260
00:14:56.730 --> 00:15:00.480
She was after the insurance money.
and even planned to frame a friend.

261
00:15:00.480 --> 00:15:03.410
Why would she be suicidal
after killing her husband?

262
00:15:03.700 --> 00:15:05.030
Who knows?

263
00:15:05.440 --> 00:15:06.870
Maybe it's out of guilt.

264
00:15:07.970 --> 00:15:09.400
That's possible.

265
00:15:10.070 --> 00:15:12.130
There was a man who committed suicide

266
00:15:12.190 --> 00:15:15.720
after killing his friend
for just 1 million won (<$1.000). too.

267
00:15:17.740 --> 00:15:19.480
Besides. suicide aside.

268
00:15:19.810 --> 00:15:21.170
many criminals visit

269
00:15:21.300 --> 00:15:24.740
their parents' graves
before they die or run away.

270
00:15:29.020 --> 00:15:30.640
Why are you so out of breath?

271
00:15:34.100 --> 00:15:35.070
What.

272
00:15:36.690 --> 00:15:38.620
need my help to build your stamina?

273
00:15:39.130 --> 00:15:40.210
No.

274
00:15:41.640 --> 00:15:45.130
Did Han Soojin
bury the weapon around here?

275
00:15:45.480 --> 00:15:46.390
Well.

276
00:15:46.650 --> 00:15:49.670
I'm not sure. But it's likely.

277
00:15:52.360 --> 00:15:53.450
Are you cold?

278
00:15:59.850 --> 00:16:01.380
Want me to warm you up?

279
00:16:01.950 --> 00:16:02.990
No!

280
